Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 27
Edition:
Quote: <i>chip at/chip away at </i>undermine someone with unpleasant criticism; originally shearing term for finding fault with work of a shearer; eg `If you keep on chipping away at him about his maths, he's going to fail everything. You know the boy's not very confident.' NZA.
